<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

    <head>
        <script src="static/star-battle.js"></script>
        <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/canvas-confetti@1.6.0/dist/confetti.browser.min.js"></script>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="./static/star-battle.css">
        <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
        <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
        <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@300&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

        <style>
            {% for regionIdx in range(10) %}
                [data-region='{{ regionIdx }}'] {
                    {% if regionIdx % 2 %}
                        background-color: {{tofino[90 - regionIdx*3]}};
                    {% else %}
                        background-color: {{tofino[15 + regionIdx*3]}};
                    {% endif %}
                }
            {% endfor %}
        </style>

    </head>

    <body>
        <div class="grid-container">
            <div class="battle-grid">
                {% for row in range(0, 10) %}
                    <div class="battle-grid-row">
                        {% for col in range(0, 10) %}
                            <div
                                class="battle-grid-cell no-icon"
                                data-row="{{ row }}"
                                data-col="{{ col }}"
                                id="cell-{{row}}-{{col}}"
                            ></div>
                        {% endfor %}
                    </div>
                {% endfor %}
                <div class="row-slider"></div>
                <div class="col-slider"></div>
            </div>

            <div class="footer">
                <div id="hint" class="icon">{% include "lightbulb-fill.svg" %}</div>
                <span id="star-count">0</span>
                <div id="rules" class="icon">{% include "journal-bookmark.svg" %}</div>
            </div>

            <div id="rules-modal" class="hidden">
                <h4>Star Battle</h4>
            Also known as Two Not Touch, this is a fun and truly addictive logic
            puzzle. The goal is to place 20 stars in the puzzle, such that
            every row, column, and colored shape contains exactly
            two stars. These stars may not be placed next to each other
            â€” not even diagonally adjacent! This is one of those rare logic
            puzzles, like Sudoku, that has extremely simple rules, yet there
            are many strategies for solving it.<br>
            
            Click each square to cycle between a star, a placehoder question mark,
            and blank.<br>
            
            Any star that shares a row, column, or region with too many other stars
            will turn into a warning triangle, letting you know you've violated a rule.<br>
            
            The counter at the bottom tells you how many stars you have placed out of
            the required total of 20 stars.<br>
            
            Click the lightbulb for a hint.
            </div>
        </div>

    </body>

</html>
